add --enable-treeterm configure option to select tree-based termination

The tree-based terminaton is more scalable than the circle-based
token passing termination, however, the tree-based method does not
yet support abort or checkpoint operations.  The user must opt-in
by specifying the configure option.

add work receipt messages for allreduce termination detection

The termination allreduce is held during the reduce-to-root phase at any process that has outstanding work transfer messages.  In addition, a process forces another allreduce iteration by setting its term_flag to 1 for the current iteration whenever it receives a work receipt message that decrements its count of outstanding work transfers.  A process that receives work adds that work to its local queue and then sends its receipt message.  This ordering ensures that the receiving process has accounted for the work by the time the receipt has been received.
